Title: Boundary detection through dynamic polygons  
Author: A. Pievatolo Peter J. Green 
Keyword: and phrases: Bayesian object restoration, probability distribution of poly gons, reversible jump MCMC computation.  
Date: Revised version, 30 May 1997  
Address: Italy.  UK.  
Affiliation: CNR-IAMI,  University of Bristol,  
Abstract: A method for the Bayesian restoration of noisy binary images portraying an object with constant greylevel on a background is presented. The restoration, performed by fitting a polygon with any number of sides to the object outline, is driven by a new probabilistic model for the generation of polygons in a compact subset of R 2 , which is used as a prior distribution for the polygon. The simulation from the prior and the calculation of the a posteriori mean of greylevels are carried out through reversible jump MCMC computation. Two examples of restoration of synthetic images are presented. 
